dnsbrute is a program to check suspicious DNS servers for incorrect or malicious
responses to queries against various domains. The responses can then be compared
against a control server (known as the Trusted server) and acted upon.

This program was written by Sicoob Confederacao employees to help organizations
whose clients are frequent victims of DNS spoofing attacks to detect and act
upon malicious servers, thus mitigating the attack. The list of authors follows:

  Felipe Scarel <felipe.scarel@sicoob.com.br, fbscarel@gmail.com>
